South Africa has recorded 1 346 new coronavirus cases. This brings the total number of cases to 663 282. The country has also recorded 126 new COVID-19 related fatalities, bringing the total number of deaths to 16 118. In a statement, Health Minister Dr Zweli Mkhize says most of the new deaths were recorded in the KwaZulu-Natal. “Regrettably, we report 126 more COVID-19 related deaths: “5 from Eastern Cape, 54 from KwaZulu-Natal, 45 from Gauteng, 5 from North West and 17 from Western Cape,” says Dr Mkhize. The cumulative number of tests conducted to date is 4 064 117. The number of recoveries now stands at 592 904, this translates to a recovery rate of 89,4%. As of today, the total number of confirmed #COVID19 cases is 663 282, the total number of deaths is 16 118 and the total number of recoveries is 592 904. pic.twitter.com/56DVjuJppo — Dr Zweli Mkhize (@DrZweliMkhize) September 22, 2020 